1Dissemination Plans0

^^^^^^^^^^We will publish the results of this work through the normal academic channels, more specifically, by attending and making presentations at the major videodisc conferences during both years.  We expect to prepare two technical papers.  The first paper will present a detailed systems description, a discussion of hardware, videodisc programming and computer software.  This paper should be possible to write at the end of the first year.  The second paper will discuss children's use of the system and will be possible at the end of the second year.  We will write one or two articles for popular journals (such as Creative Computing) and occasional news notes for organs such as Videodisc News.

^^^^^^^The word worlds machine will be a research system but one easy to replicate.  We expect the education research disc to be available only for use in a research environment; that is, we do not claim it will be suitable for general use nor that it will be free of constraints.  We believe the use of the disc will be constrained by agreements under which we will receive permission to use copyrighted material in our research environment.  Nonetheless, the word worlds machine should be sufficiently accessible for demonstration to commercial videodisc programming developers that it could have significant impact through shaping their subsequent designs.
